key Findings:-¶

In [69]:
# We have analysed the dataset through --> 

#Professional Status:- The key professional status categories were "Causes," "Means Adopted," "Professional Profile," "Education Status," and "Social Status."
#The most significant category was "Causes" with 458 cases.

# Age Group Analysis:-The age groups "15-29," "30-44," and "60-75" had the highest number of suicide cases.
#  The age group "75+" had the lowest number of cases. 

#Reasons Analysis:- The reasons behind suicides were explored, with categories such as "Poverty," "Service (Private)," and "By Over Alcoholism."
# The top reason was "Others (Please Specify)" with 27 cases.

#Gender Analysis:- There were 504 cases of males and 496 cases of females, indicating a nearly equal distribution.

#Yearly Analysis:- The year "2011" had the highest number of suicide cases, followed closely by "2005."

#State-wise Analysis:- "Goa" had the highest number of suicide cases, followed by "Madhya Pradesh" and "Chandigarh."
